value.0: What would you make of my time? Speak quickly, for I have much to do.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> W-what? I am a Helmite in service to Desther! Do you know what you risk by threatening me?!
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> Wait! No... no I don't wish to make a scene. I have... important work that must not be interrupted. Fine, you may have your gold... but...

Comment.value: Already been shaken down for gold

value.0: If you are a master of weapons, the Shining Knight Arms and Armor in the City Core seem to be well-stocked.
I have also heard of a mercenary enclave that hires out henchmen. It is the Trade of Blades in the City Core, but I would avoid it.
If you know of arcane magic, the Cloak Tower may assist you. It is just inside the Beggar's Nest.
Our Helmite Temple is closed while we continue our blessings. The Temple of Tyr in the City Core will assist you.
Are you a servant of nature? There is a Druid Tree in the Docks district, though I am unfamiliar with them.
I believe the different regions are the Beggar's Nest, the Docks, the Blacklake district, the prison, and the City Core.
Ah, the prison. Try as we might, we Helmites have not been allowed much access within.
